content: good app

I'm a front-end web developer, and I can attest that Jon provides the best customer service I've experienced in 20+ years in the field. The app itself is easy to use, accurate, comprehensive, and simply a brilliant idea to download the trails before you get into those canyons. Well done, sir!
replyContent:
Wow! Best review ever. Thank you so very much. It's feedback like this that keeps up going. Kind words indeed.
Keep on Hiking :)

content: I totally love this app. The trail descriptions and tips are very helpful and accurate. Having GPS guidance to trailheads and the locator to plot exactly where you are on the trail make getting lost either on the way to, or on the trail, highly unlikely. I don't usually pay for apps, but I'm glad I made an exception for this one!
replyContent: Thanks for the review! Glad you find the app helpful, and very happy you decided to hike with us!

content: Very limiting app. I'm a runner and just want a phone version of all Sedona trails on a map with my GPS dot. I want to be able to see the maps before downloading, and I want to be able to see multiple "hikes" at a time on a map. The map is the most important part of an app like this and it's an afterthought here. I don't care about all the text/descriptions, I just want a trail map!!
replyContent: Sorry you're runner and purchased a hiking app. I'm sorry you gave our hiking app a 2 star rating because it's not a running app. Apples and oranges.

content: Excellent app! Very helpful!!
replyContent: Thank you! Glad we can be helpful in you enjoying the beauty of the Sedona area!

content: Horrible and i cant believe i bought it
replyContent: Sorry you're not happy. You can get a refund. And if you have/are experiencing problems we can help. Really, we can. Please send us a note and we can get things squared away.

content: I have used this excellent app twice while hiking in Sedona during two separate March Breaks. We are going to Sedona again this March so we will make use of it again. I would also recommend using it with an area map, Google Maps (you can download google maps onto your device so you don't need cellular access) or my favourite topo map app Gaia GPS. Again, you can download maps onto your device negating the need for cellular access.
replyContent: Marko - Thanks for the great review. When we set out creating this app, cell phone coverage was pretty sparse in Sedona so Google Maps wasn't very useful. Now, on trails with cellular coverage Google Maps can be a great  addition to your hiking experience. Thanks again! We appreciate it.

content: Great app - especially if you're a new visitor to Sedona and looking to do some hiking. Pair this app with an area map from a visitor center or the chamber of commerce and you should be set. The two used together make finding your way around much easier . The app itself worked flawlessly on my Android phone and judging from the few hikes we took, their hike descriptions are very good. Highly recommended, and probably the cheapest thing you will purchase during your stay in Sedona. Happy trails to all.
replyContent: Thanks for the review! We are certainly glad you find the app useful. Please don't hesitate to get a hold of us with any questions you might have. Try the AllAppTrails download for an overview map of the trailheads as well. Thanks!

content: Won't download hikes to tablet and email attempts to get support are blocked by APP. No phone support provided.
replyContent: Sorry you are having difficulties. Nine time out of ten download problems are caused by a poor network connection. Finding a better network solves that. The app can't block your email, we use whatever you have configured as the client on your Android device. So find a good strong network and try it again. support@SedonaHikingApp.com. We can help.

content: Use this app whenever in Sedona. Nice to have never knew there were so many hiking options.
replyContent: Thank you for the review. We're happy you are find it useful. Hike away!

content: Made our time in Sedona much more relaxing, efficient, and fun by helping us to find the right hikes and feel confident that we wouldn't get lost driving there and while on the trail. App navigation is a bit unusual, and interface is not the slickest but that is part of its charm. A worthwhile investment.
The  app keeps freezing up after downloading one trail. I  had  to  keep  uninstalling and  reinstalling. Very  frustrating.
replyContent:
If you contact us we could have helped.  Really.
support@SedonaHikingApp.com

content: Great app and good support when needed
When I first tried to get maps saw elev profile or nothing be patient they are probably still downloading
replyContent:
Glad it is working for you!  Thanks for being patient.
If assistance is needed please email support@SedonaHikingApp.com.  We are happy to help!

content: Great app design, intuitive features, a must have for hikers who like smartphones. This app sets the standard for hiking apps. Would love to see this app include maps for Prescott and other Arizona locations especially because of all the additional features that other mapping apps do not have.
Simple and informative

Some books and webpages like to obscure the names of the hikes to get you to buy before you find out where and what the hikes are. The website compliments the app and the app works without any network access, which is critical. The combination of this app and a topo map really helped make our Sedona hiking vacation a success.

This is the app you want!  Following trails is easy with this genius app.  It makes hiking in Sedona so much more enjoyable because you don't have to use a paper map.  All the trail information is on my phone so it's easy to take with us.   The trail descriptions and points of interest are not too wordy, they are 'just right' which allows you to concentrate on the beauty of Sedona.  I mean, that's why you are hiking....to enjoy the beauty!  Good job with this app.  Highly recommend this one!
My family recently hit the trails and used this app to easily navigate the Sedona paths. We had never visited the area before and found this to be an excellent resour e.

This was fun to have a green dot tell me where I was on the trail. The key point information is very helpful for staying on the trail. No more wondering which way to go! My husband and I enjoyed the photos and looking for the same scenes along the way. We found the maps very precise and on target with the real trail. We had no idea there were so many trails to explore. This is so much more convenient than a hiking book, and cheaper! What a great resource we have found that will inspire me to go back and hike some more! Thank you!

This is an indispensable app for experienced and inexperienced hikers alike. I have personally hiked over a dozen trails around Sedona, and even though I am a seasoned hiker, I have had trouble trail - finding on many of these trails. Some of the issues include out of date trail books, poor trail signage, and unmarked trail intersections. This app keeps you right on the trail eliminating wasted time and much angst. This is the best $4.99 any Sedona hiker could ever spend!!
Selecting "Take a hike" crashes app on Nexus 7.
replyContent: This issue affecting Android Version 4.2  was fixed in Version 1.16. We apologize for any inconvenience.  If you have problems please contact support through our website.

content: Great pictures and descriptions. Look forward to using this on the trails.
